\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1\cb3\highlight3	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1\cb3\highlight3 This creates both opportunities and challenges for creators of these works - producing 'resonant' characters (i.e. those from which Oatley's simulation can be run satisfactorily) is difficult, because so much more needs to be simulated/built (creative burden), much more complicated, work within the mechanical/digital system of the experience, work well with the player's input. So much more can go wrong in the transmission/conversation between, and we do not have a good grammar/techniques, yet, for producing beings - the grammars are being developed for other things, and more traditional techniques ladled on top, or the idea of character.}
